Coming from Atlassian support ticket CSP-95089 I want to point out the decicive relevance of the following:
Quite urgently I need an opportunity to display layered graphical content on wiki-pages and to have an easy-to-use editor comparable to MS PowerPoint for keeping track of necessary changes in graphical content. Wiki technology allows this so far perfectly for text, simple bitmaps and hyperlinks. But there is no way to handle layered graphics as usual in PowerPoint slides adequately in an article. Workarounds with FlashPlayer and attached office files make things worse. This development may be stopped as soon as layered graphic content can be uploaded into articles with no effort for the user.
Please put this issue into the adequate project. I'm sure this would be the ultimate promotion for Confluence, because we are facing this point as major obstacle for user acceptance.

