h3. Problem Definition

Currently the Logging and Profiling guide: [Logging and Profiling|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver071/logging-and-profiling-802592962.html] does not disclose how to add a package and set it's logging level. 

h3. Suggested Solution
Documentation that explains how to set logging levels for packages that are not listed on the logging and profiling page. 


h3. Workaround
Simply use the "Configure logging level for another package." on the Logging and Profiling page: {{<BASE-URL>/secure/admin/ViewLogging.jspa}} to configure additional packages and their logging levels. 

Alternatively set the logging level by calling: {{<BASE-URL>/secure/admin/ConfigureLogging.jspa?loggerName=<PACKAGE>&levelName=<LEVEL>}}

