h3. Problem Definition

Currently Tomcat threads have no easy way of being mapped back to a URI. Mapping them back makes it easier to understand what's spawning, or using the thread.

h3. Suggested Solution

Enhance the logging such that there's a filter in place that will provide additional information. For example:

{noformat}
"http-bio-8080-exec-25 uri:/secure/admin/views/integritycheckercorrect.jsp username:admin" #156 daemon prio=5 os_prio=31 tid=0x00007fe67f669800 nid=0x5f0f runnable [0x0000700006bcb000]
{noformat}

h3. Workaround 

Install the https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/com.atlassian.ams.shipit.tomcat-filter/server/overview add-on.

