The [email handler documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiracloud/creating-issues-and-comments-from-email-779288896.html#Creatingissuesandcommentsfromemail-messagehandlersMailhandlers] for [Create a new issue from each email message|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiracloud/creating-issues-and-comments-from-email-779288896.html#Creatingissuesandcommentsfromemail-Createanewissuefromeachemailmessage] is wrong. Indeed, for the *Project* field, it says:
{quote}
*Project*	
Specify the project key of the default project to which new issues are created by this handler — for example, JRA.
+Note:+
This field is only relevant for issue creation, not for issue commenting.
If an email message contains an issue key in its subject line and that issue key exists in your JIRA installation, the handler will add the email message content as a comment on the issue, regardless of which project the issue is in. 
{quote}

The above text is the same as the one for [Create a new issue or add a comment to an existing issue|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiracloud/creating-issues-and-comments-from-email-779288896.html#Creatingissuesandcommentsfromemail-Createanewissueoraddacommenttoanexistingissue], but then if that was the case there wouldn't be any difference among the 2.

Indeed, if I reply to a notification from ISSUE-A, I have the email handler configured to ["Create a new issue from each email message"|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiracloud/creating-issues-and-comments-from-email-779288896.html#Creatingissuesandcommentsfromemail-Createanewissuefromeachemailmessage] and the *Project* field is set to PROJECT-Y. Then my reply will create a new issue in PROJECT-Y instead of adding a comment to ISSUE-A.

