h3. Summary

When you click on *Issues* the following entry is added to the logs:

{noformat}
2016-04-07 15:32:16,377 http-nio-8080-exec-25 WARN pcora 932x269x1 1cozpr3 0:0:0:0:0:0:0:1 /rest/api/1.0/menus/find_link [c.a.j.i.search.util.SearchPropertiesManager] Invalid filter ID in user preferences:
{noformat}

h3. Steps to Reproduce

# Login to JIRA, click on Search for Issues and do nothing (don't search for any issues or choose a filter). You can click on an issue if the Issue Navigator had issues as this does not affects the bug.
# Logout and Login again and click on *Issues*. The log will get:
{noformat}
2016-04-07 15:32:16,377 http-nio-8080-exec-25 WARN pcora 932x269x1 1cozpr3 0:0:0:0:0:0:0:1 /rest/api/1.0/menus/find_link [c.a.j.i.search.util.SearchPropertiesManager] Invalid filter ID in user preferences:
{noformat}

h3. Expected Results

Nothing is added to the logs.

h3. Actual Results

The exception above is added to the logs.
 
h3. Notes

It seems that when you click on *Search for Issues* the properties that store the *Current Search* are cleared and if you don't do a search or click on a filter, nothing will be recoded and the next time JIRA checks for it, the WARN will be thrown in the logs.

