I have multiple service desks.. i need to be able to push out reports where i can see a lot of information in one place.  I like the look of the Projects gadget. However, i need to see more than just if there is an open ticket.  I would like to see if there is an open ticket and a number beside it showing how many there are and also how many were closed for a period of time i pick (monthly, quarterly, etc..).  Also,  have tried using the _recently created_ chart with filters to show how many tickets were opened and closed for a time period.  However, when a month is over it doesn't stop reporting for that time.  For instance, when a ticket is opened in March and closed in April, the closing of the ticket gets reported in March!  There should be a way to see this happened in March, now that it's april you have this many tickets open from last month, this many tickets that have been opened this month and when a ticket is closed report it closed in the correct month.  I added 2 screen shots so you can see what i currently have and hopefully this will help in understanding what i am looking for.  So, far the reporting i have been able to find useful is barely useful.  I really hope you can enhance this.

