Sometimes, when I create a new bug and have started typing into the text fields, I realize I don't really need to file this bug (e.g. because I'm filing it against the wrong project or so). So I click "Cancel". The dialog that comes up then asks whether I really want to leave and shows "Cancel" or "OK" as choices.

I never know which one to do. I just clicked "Cancel" so by all means clicking "Cancel" again should do what I told it to. Or is it "OK" as in "Yes I want to cancel the creation"?

Please rename the buttons. I'd suggest already renaming the original "Cancel" button under "Create Issue" to "Discard", then in the confirmation offering "Keep" or "Discard" as choices, and making sure to ask "Do you really want to Discard this bug? Any information you've entered will be lost" or so.

